Responsibilities:

Execute and implement strategic business plan to achieve objectives (short, medium and long term);
Oversee the daily operational activities;
Coordinate the human and materials resources of the Chinese medicine clinics;
Formulate polices and coordinate methods to ensure patient satisfaction;
Perform ad hoc projects and assignment as required.

Requirements:

Bachelor’s degree in Pharmacy, Chinese medicine or equivalent;
5 years or above experience in pharmacy or Chinese medicines industry of which at least 2 years management experience;
Strong industry network with a solid track record of proven ability to operate clinic;
Good command of spoken and written English & Chinese (Cantonese & Putonghua);
Have a startup mindset, well-organized, open-minded, decisive and flexible.

We offer 5-day work week and competitive remuneration package to qualified candidates. Interested parties please send your resume with current and expected salary for application. Please visit our company’s website www.tianda.com to know more about us.

Data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.  Applicants not heard from us within 6 weeks may consider their applications filed for future openings.

Job Descriptions

Manage full spectrum of recruitment services, including but not limited to interviewing candidates, understanding their' needs, assessing and identifying the right candidates;
Translate business requirements into recruitment practices and deliver solutions aligned with business objectives;
Source and evaluate the effectiveness of advertising and recruitment channel;
Responsible for sales management of the team including hiring, training and performance evaluation.

 Job Requirements

Bachelor’s degree holder, with major in relevant sector preferable;
Possess excellent presentation and influencing skills to advise candidate at all levels in a professional manner;
Excellent command in English, Mandarin and Cantonese.

 Benefits

Basic salary up to 25,000 + competitive commission;
Comprehensive training programs;
Excellent career path;
Remuneration negotiable.

Candidates without recruitment or sales experience but have the right motivation and attitude are welcomed. Training will be provided.

