We are now looking for a Senior Manager who will be responsible for business development and international programmes of the Hong Kong Arts Development Council. He/she reports directly to the Chief Executive and assists in devising, implementing and evaluation of large-scale activities. He/she will be a leader of several teams in carrying out proactive projects and schemes under his/her charge.

Requirements:

University degree with at least 8 years of relevant full-time working experience in arts and culture, including project management experience;
Strong administrative, analytical and strategy development capacity and skills;
Excellent communication skills in both written and spoken English and Chinese;
Strong sense of responsibility, self-motivation and an aptitude for innovation and change;
Proven achievements that demonstrate professional capabilities in organization, arts administration, proactiveness and people management;
Readiness to work under pressure and deliver work of the highest quality;
Proficiency in PC operations (MS Office applications and Chinese Word Processing);
Previous experience with NGOs and public organisations will be an added value

Salary offered will be commensurate with qualifications and experience. Interested persons please send CV with details on education and work experience, stating salary history and expected salary, and indicating your earliest availability to the Human Resources Department, 10/F, 1063 King’s Road, Quarry Bay, Hong Kong no later than 4 February 2022. Please quote the job reference on the envelope.

Applicants not invited for interview within 16 weeks from the closing date for application may assume that their applications are unsuccessful. Personal data collected will be treated in strictest confidence and will only be used for recruitment purposes. HKADC reserves the right to consider late applications and not to make appointment for the post advertised. We do not accept applications through e-mail or fax.

HKADC is an Equal Opportunities Employer

Reporting to the Director and working closely with senior management, the incumbent will be responsible for leading the Public Relations & Communications Department in the planning and implementation of internal and external communications inclusive event and brand management, brand and engagement programmes and media management.


Responsibilities:


Formulate and implement comprehensive public relations & communication strategies and plans to position the Welfare Council as an innovative and caring organization in social welfare sector;
Design and produce materials to effectively communicate the Welfare Council’s vision, mission, values and programme activities to general public;
Build up a brand awareness and enhance the image of the Welfare Council via different social media, events, campaigns and programmes, its services, activities and research, for enhancement of its reputation in the community;
Work closely with Resources Development Department to formulate fund raising strategies and establish relationship with donors and the community;
Develop and maintain professional network, and maintain relationships with external partners, stakeholders and mass media;
Liaise and communicate with the media, and manage media activitiesincluding press invitation, press releases and conferences, briefings, interviews, etc.;
Serve as media advisor in crisis management.

Requirements :

Bachelor degree or above in Public Relations / Marketing / Communications or related disciplines
Minimum 8 years’ relevant and solid experience in journalism, corporate communications or public relations, preferably with experiences in social services sector or non-governmental organization
Able to explore complex ideas and turn it to comprehensive and interesting story
Self-motivated, out-going, presentable and creative person, with good analytical and organizing skills
Good command of both spoken and written English, Cantonese and Mandarin
Experience in digital media communication and staff supervision is preferred
Candidates with less experience will be considered as Public Relations & Communications Manager

Two-year contract will be offered as a start. Candidates with satisfactory performance will be reappointed to permanent post after the first contract.



Interested parties please apply with full curriculum vitae with Expected Salary and Available Date to Human Resources Department, Hong Kong Sheng Kung Hui Welfare Council, 5/F, Marina House, 68 Hing Man Street, Shaukeiwan, Hong Kong or click "Apply Now". Please indicate the reference number on the envelope.

Applications will be reviewed upon receiving and continue until 7 February 2022 or until the post is filled. All applications will be treated in strict confidence for the recruitment purpose only.  Candidates not invited for interview within 8 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful, and the application papers will be retained for a maximum period of 6 months.

Reporting to the Senior Management, the appointee will provide leadership and management of the Employment and ERB services of the Agency, which includes but not limited to the overall planning and development of services with different funding modes (government subsidised, non-government funders and self-financing, etc), implementing innovative programmes in response to current and emerging service trend and social needs, promotion of effective stakeholder relationship and networking, as well as mobilising available resources for the service advancement and development.

 Requirements

Post-secondary education preferably with Bachelor degree in Social Work or Business discipline;
Registered Social Worker with minimum 7 years’ work experience preferably in employment / ERB or related services plus over 4 years’ supervisory / management and service development experience;
Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Strong leadership and people management with good presentation, collaboration, networking and organisational skills;
Dynamic and resourceful with proven ability to network and foster relationships, both internally and externally, work efficiently under pressure and multi-tasks oriented;
Excellent working knowledge on employment marketing, training and enhancement; and
Computer literate and able to pick up new technologies and innovative concepts quickly.

 Appointment will be made on contract term with staff benefits including training subsidies, medical benefits. Qualified candidates are invited to submit application letter and full resume with present and expected salary and earliest availability.

(All information provided will be kept as confidential & only be used for recruitment related purposes)

