You will be responsible for:


assisting with managing and monitoring the OPEX for park operations, including expenses for the park ambassadors team, autonomous vehicle etc;
providing input to regular financial reporting;
preparing documents in support of the team’s procurement and payment needs in compliance with the related guidelines of the Authority;
drafting and implementing open space related policies, guidelines, procedures to ensure effective, smooth and efficient performance of public open spaces across the district;
handling the day-to-day management of the Park and Public Open Space;
building good relationship with internal and external key stakeholders including the general public, community groups, NGOs, event organisers and relevant government departments, etc;
ensuring the required performance level of service providers is achieved;
working closely with the Facilities Management Team and Landscaping Team to ensure we have the right facilities to enhance the visitor experience in the Park, as well as creating an attractive working environment for our staff;
assisting in the implementation of branding initiatives;
assisting in the development and implementation of education and community programmes, including school activities; and
monitoring customer feedback and identify areas of improvements with an overall objective to enhance visitors experience.

You should:


possess a recognised university degree in recreation management / facilities management or equivalent;
have 5 years of experience in the operation and management park or other form of open space / visitor destinations / event management, preferably in sizeable organisations or public sector;
demonstrate good teamwork, interpersonal and communication skills with the ability to effectively interact with all levels of internal and external stakeholders;
be pleasant, mature, committed, highly organized, attention to details with good analytical skills, and able to work independently and under pressure;
ability to work under pressure, and a willingness to take on new challenges and to work over the weekend and/or public holiday to support park operations if required;
possess strong communication and presentation skills and the ability to effectively interact with internal and external personnel at all levels; and
be proficient in written and spoken English and Chinese.
For interested parties, please submit your application with detailed CV on or before 20 January 2022. Applicants are encouraged to submit their applications as soon as possible. The review of applications will continue until post is filled.



Data collected will only be used for job application processing. Your data may be accessed by our appointed recruitment consultants who have agreed to keep confidence of all personal data in not less than the standards applicable to us. Applicants not being invited for interview within 4 weeks from the submission date may assume their applications unsuccessful.

All related information will be kept up to 24 months and all personal data will be destroyed afterwards.

