Achieving sales targets/ priorities  through promoting Toll products and services to existing and potential customers, and drive quality services throughout the process; keep continuous sales growth;
Collaborate with manager to ensure alignment with strategies in forecasting, business planning and pipeline development;
Implement Sales & Marketing Strategy in line with TGF to optimize the company’s capabilities & resources by attracting / identifying new opportunities and retaining current customers;
Upsell additional services to the existing customer base in order to increase sales volumes and revenues;
Continually explore qualified new customers, prepare and follow-up quotations and generate sales leads; Work with network to identify import and export opportunities;
Monitor and respond to concerned parties to ensure accurate, timely and positive customer experience delivery;
Maintain, monitor and ensure all sales activities are complied with Toll compliances, relevant polices and governances;
Perform all aspects of the sales process and incorporate daily use in sales management system platform to document sales activity and relevant customer business details;
Support to review contracts, and ensure the terms & processes are complied with company compliances & relevant policies;
Support to perform market research and analysis on rate trends and understanding rate trends / support to work on pricing strategies internally; maintain right pricing strategies to improve winning ratio;
Cooperate with Credit Department to collect / settle outstanding overdue payments from customers;
Attend regular sales meeting to understand market intelligences, Toll products & sales programs, and always keep updated readiness for sales developments;   
Customer visits with occasional travel to China (mainly South China);
Support to identify & drive safety measures in relationship to clients’ shipments / cargoes packaging
Minimum 5 years relevant working experience in sales or business development in logistics / freight forwarding industries.
Strategic thinking and strong networking abilities;
Analytical skills and sensible to market trends;
Experience in using CRM system;
With Global freight forwarding experiences;
Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Outlook).
